2026-06-04 13:47:51,600 | DEBUG    |   ## Root cause
2026-06-04 13:47:51,600 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:47:51,600 | DEBUG    |   `AsciiJSON.Render` in `render/json.go` escapes every rune above `unicode.MaxASCII` with `fmt.Appendf(..., "\\u%04x", r)`. For `%04x`, width 4 is a **minimum**, not a maximum. Code points above U+FFFF (non-BMP, e.g. emoji) format to five or more hex digits, producing invalid JSON escapes like `\u1f600` instead of the RFC 8259–required UTF-16 surrogate pair (`\ud83d\ude00` for U+1F600). Decoders treat only four hex digits per `\u`, so the extra digit(s) become literal characters and the string no longer round-trips.
2026-06-04 13:47:51,600 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:47:51,600 | DEBUG    |   BMP non-ASCII (U+0080–U+FFFF), including existing CJK tests, are unaffected because they always fit in four hex digits.
2026-06-04 13:47:51,600 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:47:51,600 | DEBUG    |   ## Proposed fix
2026-06-04 13:47:51,600 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:47:51,600 | DEBUG    |   In the `r > unicode.MaxASCII` branch of `AsciiJSON.Render`:
2026-06-04 13:47:51,600 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:47:51,600 | DEBUG    |   1. **BMP (r ≤ 0xFFFF):** keep current behavior — single `\u%04x` escape (unchanged output for existing callers).
2026-06-04 13:47:51,601 | DEBUG    |   2. **Supplementary (r > 0xFFFF):** use `unicode/utf16.EncodeRune(r)` to obtain high and low surrogates, then emit **two** four-digit escapes: `\u%04x\u%04x` (e.g. U+1F600 → `\ud83d\ude00`).
2026-06-04 13:47:51,601 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:47:51,601 | DEBUG    |   Adjust the reusable `escapeBuf` slice capacity from 6 to **12** bytes (two `\uXXXX` sequences) and update the comment accordingly. No changes to `Context.AsciiJSON`, content-type handling, or marshaling — only the post-marshal ASCII-escaping loop.
2026-06-04 13:47:51,601 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:47:51,601 | DEBUG    |   **Assumption:** Gin intends RFC 8259–compliant `\u` escaping (same as `encoding/json`), not a custom encoding scheme.
2026-06-04 13:47:51,601 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:47:51,601 | DEBUG    |   ## Files to change
2026-06-04 13:47:51,601 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:47:51,601 | DEBUG    |   | File | Change |
2026-06-04 13:47:51,601 | DEBUG    |   |------|--------|
2026-06-04 13:47:51,601 | DEBUG    |   | `render/json.go` | Fix surrogate-pair escaping in `AsciiJSON.Render`; add `unicode/utf16` import; bump `escapeBuf` cap/comment |
2026-06-04 13:47:51,601 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:47:51,601 | DEBUG    |   No other files are required for the fix. `context.go` / `docs/doc.md` / `CHANGELOG.md` are optional follow-ups, not part of the minimal bug fix.
