2026-06-04 13:48:07,169 | DEBUG    |   ## Root cause
2026-06-04 13:48:07,169 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:48:07,169 | DEBUG    |   `AsciiJSON.Render` in `render/json.go` escapes every rune above `unicode.MaxASCII` with `fmt.Appendf(..., "\\u%04x", r)`. For `%04x`, width 4 is a **minimum**, not a maximum. Code points above U+FFFF (non-BMP, e.g. emoji) format to five or more hex digits, producing invalid JSON escapes like `\u1f600` instead of the RFC 8259–required UTF-16 surrogate pair (`\ud83d\ude00` for U+1F600). Decoders treat only four hex
