2026-06-04 13:50:15,822 | DEBUG    |   ## Issue
2026-06-04 13:50:15,822 | DEBUG    |   **AsciiJSON silently corrupts non-BMP characters (emoji) by emitting malformed \u escapes** — https://github.com/gin-gonic/gin/issues/4688
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   ### Description
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   `render.AsciiJSON` corrupts any Unicode code point above U+FFFF (non-BMP characters such as emoji). It escapes every non-ASCII rune with `fmt.Appendf(buf, "\\u%04x", r)`, but `%04x` is a *minimum* width, not a fixed width. A non-BMP rune needs 5+ hex digits, so a single 5-digit `\uXXXXX` token is written. JSON `\u` escapes are **exactly 4 hex digits**, so a decoder reads the first 4 as one character and the trailing digit(s) as literal text.
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   The output is still *syntactically valid* JSON (so this is not a parse error and is easy to miss), but the value is silently wrong — it does not round-trip.
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   Per RFC 8259 §7, code points outside the BMP must be encoded as a UTF-16 surrogate pair (e.g. U+1F600 → `\ud83d\ude00`).
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   **Example — `😀` (U+1F600):**
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   | | value |
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   |---|---|
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   | Input | `😀` |
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   | `AsciiJSON` output | `{"msg":"\u1f600"}` |
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   | After `json.Unmarshal` | `ὠ0`  (U+1F60 `ὠ` + literal `0`) |
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   | Expected after round-trip | `😀` |
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   Offending code — `render/json.go` (`AsciiJSON.Render`):
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   ```go
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   for _, r := range bytesconv.BytesToString(ret) {
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |       if r > unicode.MaxASCII {
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |           escapeBuf = fmt.Appendf(escapeBuf[:0], "\\u%04x", r) // 5+ digits for non-BMP → invalid escape
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |           buffer.Write(escapeBuf)
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |       } else {
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |           buffer.WriteByte(byte(r))
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |       }
2026-06-04 13:50:15,823 | DEBUG    |   }
