2026-06-04 13:50:15,824 | DEBUG    |   ## Fix plan
2026-06-04 13:50:15,824 | DEBUG    |   ## Root cause
2026-06-04 13:50:15,824 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:50:15,824 | DEBUG    |   `AsciiJSON.Render` in `render/json.go` escapes every rune above `unicode.MaxASCII` with `fmt.Appendf(..., "\\u%04x", r)`. For `%04x`, width 4 is a **minimum**, not a maximum. Code points above U+FFFF (non-BMP, e.g. emoji) format to five or more hex digits, producing invalid JSON escapes like `\u1f600` instead of the RFC 8259–required UTF-16 surrogate pair (`\ud83d\ude00` for U+1F600). Decoders treat only four hex digits per `\u`, so the extra digit(s) become literal characters and the string no longer round-trips.
2026-06-04 13:50:15,824 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:50:15,824 | DEBUG    |   BMP non-ASCII (U+0080–U+FFFF), including existing CJK tests, are unaffected because they always fit in four hex digits.
2026-06-04 13:50:15,824 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:50:15,824 | DEBUG    |   ## Proposed fix
2026-06-04 13:50:15,824 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:50:15,824 | DEBUG    |   In the `r > unicode.MaxASCII` branch of `AsciiJSON.Render`:
2026-06-04 13:50:15,824 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:50:15,824 | DEBUG    |   1. **BMP (r ≤ 0xFFFF):** keep current behavior — single `\u%04x` escape (unchanged output for existing
2026-06-04 13:50:15,824 | DEBUG    | --- pr_writer — response ---
2026-06-04 13:50:15,824 | DEBUG    |   # Fix AsciiJSON non-BMP Unicode escaping via UTF-16 surrogate pairs
2026-06-04 13:50:15,824 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:50:15,824 | DEBUG    |   ## Summary
2026-06-04 13:50:15,824 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:50:15,824 | DEBUG    |   `render.AsciiJSON` corrupts supplementary-plane characters (e.g. emoji) by emitting invalid `\u` escapes. It uses `fmt.Appendf(..., "\\u%04x", r)`, where `%04x` is a minimum width, so code points above U+FFFF produce five or more hex digits (e.g. `\u1f600` for 😀). JSON requires exactly four hex digits per `\u` escape; decoders read only four digits and treat the rest as literal text, so the value is silently wrong and does not round-trip.
2026-06-04 13:50:15,825 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:50:15,825 | DEBUG    |   This PR keeps single `\u%04x` escapes for BMP non-ASCII runes (unchanged for existing CJK/HTML output) and encodes supplementary-plane runes as RFC 8259 UTF-16 surrogate pairs via `unicode/utf16.EncodeRune`, emitting two four-digit escapes (e.g. U+1F600 → `\ud83d\ude00`).
2026-06-04 13:50:15,825 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:50:15,825 | DEBUG    |   ## Changes
2026-06-04 13:50:15,825 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:50:15,825 | DEBUG    |   - **`render/json.go`**: In `AsciiJSON.Render`, branch on `r > 0xFFFF` to emit surrogate-pair escapes with `utf16.EncodeRune`; keep single `\u%04x` for BMP runes above ASCII.
2026-06-04 13:50:15,825 | DEBUG    |   - **`render/json.go`**: Import `unicode/utf16`; increase reusable `escapeBuf` capacity from 6 to 12 bytes for two `\uXXXX` sequences.
2026-06-04 13:50:15,825 | DEBUG    |   - **`render/render_test.go`**: Extend `TestRenderAsciiJSON` with emoji regression (body `{"msg":"\ud83d\ude00"}` and `json.Unmarshal` round-trip), boundary at U+FFFF (single `\uffff`), and U+10000 (first supplementary code point, `\ud800\udc00` with round-trip).
2026-06-04 13:50:15,825 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:50:15,825 | DEBUG    |   ## Test plan
